topic.title: High Speed Serial Interfaces

entry.p: The PCIe differential receivers are broken up by Stack (x) and Lane (15:0) where x=0,1,2,3,4,5. Each receiver has an integrated resistive termination and programmable equalization.
Stacks are enabled for each variants as follows:

The PCIe differential transmitters are broken up by Stack (x) and Lane (15:0) where x=0,1,2,3,4,5. Each transmitter has an integrated resistive termination, configurable pre-emphasis and transmit swing features. It requires an external AC-coupling capacitor.
Stacks are enabled for each variants as follows:

row.entry:
These lanes are part of Stack 6 and are unique in that they are x1 bifurcation capable (4x1). This makes them ideal for use as management lanes but are also usable for any PCIe application.
Applicable to the following variants:
100-Lane
84-Lane
68-Lane
52-Lane
36-Lane
28-Lane
Each receiver has an integrated resistive termination.
When using these lanes in x1 bifurcation mode, CutThrough DMA cannot be used.
